{"id": "067ba4e1c4708355821874d6c7509914a8f30ca17d332310a4ad554b1135a1c6", "item_id": "58e210552b:0", "text": "PxrIntMultLightFilter is a light filter that allows you to multiply the intensity/exposure of the light. This is very useful when you want to isolate a particular asset(s) from the rest of the scene that has different intensity/exposure. This is via linking the objects to the PxrIntMultLightFilter. You can now guide your viewer using light intensity!"}
{"id": "88fb11573a6a01055cff4da5a1b81f5b20850faa77b8ca6826ef9d278b150d20", "item_id": "58e210552b:2", "text": "Multiplier"}
{"id": "a6d01dcff3bfd333edf90a50daac2104cefab98b85bdbba67c8209ab75eb6447", "item_id": "58e210552b:3", "text": "Intensity"}
{"id": "b73d2f2d679e6a61d2fd9eeff7705b8d319a143943ad84ce7e7029b14bcc65f8", "item_id": "58e210552b:4", "text": "Multiplier for the light intensity."}
{"id": "392c441cfe7c4465e1f01f9079fe2c5cc2977d1f61951471acb640bba8fa1537", "item_id": "58e210552b:6", "text": "Exposure control for the multiplier."}
{"id": "7e04f2ffb9334e3d19a15c949a73818d4b271b0e713dbfad612b29491b46bc1b", "item_id": "58e210552b:7", "text": "Invert"}
{"id": "cade95bec0142dff5a4e1ccbfb51084867747d851fd7b7e7665645fba7c921b0", "item_id": "58e210552b:8", "text": "Invert the multiplier."}
{"id": "7d1e39756f69b3f2761ce3348e380161b58896ed182493fe87796e8a6a85a0ee", "item_id": "58e210552b:10", "text": "Controls the strength of this light filter."}
{"id": "347fd578167c6bc809620bb574d4772c7a1dc176c7a932272a5b32e3c8b0d652", "item_id": "58e210552b:11", "text": "Diffuse"}
{"id": "f7bc5406b76b6b31f82e6a04a53b693cce61fd2a59a3387aa10cf8a79f42ac3a", "item_id": "58e210552b:12", "text": "Controls the amount of diffuse contribution."}
{"id": "2b23ae6b78b7d463bfe2504b11e8b8f11223c65278da7b3ae2ebf248cc2e10ae", "item_id": "58e210552b:13", "text": "Specular"}
{"id": "0729653839660abd73249d6f711688f2cd32b059f2dd8ff621d60c41a7b68c08", "item_id": "58e210552b:14", "text": "Controls the amount of specular contribution."}
{"id": "48de4ea6f0cda336fe83df053fc7728df8722a9303d28dbd1920bf80c9cba637", "item_id": "58e210552b:16", "text": "Acts as a multiplier for the color saturation of the light. Allowing you to increase or reduce the saturation."}
{"id": "6a822da0d9dba4226f885efe81fad17f016a6d36f2befee7891981b3814f4514", "item_id": "58e210552b:17", "text": "Tint"}
{"id": "c377a53849ca01d97344506599e7973fd9cd74ae234c748f35ca800ab324ede8", "item_id": "58e210552b:18", "text": "Tint of the light color after saturation."}
{"id": "f1d391844bc65573f53c0c894750b2c4c7b5a63f81897dc2d03474e6c877f728", "item_id": "58e210552b:19", "text": "Combine Mode"}
{"id": "6c4e6482ef6f1c59879c2cf50aa7119c8cb3b2270c5a8853659f467c915f0df8", "item_id": "58e210552b:20", "text": "Combine mode for PxrIntMultLightFilter is always multiplied."}
